course_metadata.title: Housing: Thermal performance of well-insulated building envelopes

content_chunks.content: Within the framework of this course the thermal performance of well-insulated building envelopes is examined in a detailed manner, emphasizing energy efficiency, material properties, design considerations, and practical applications. Students will gain knowledge and analytical skills into the principles of heat transfer, thermal properties of materials, and the building insulation materials, technologies. The course includes case studies and exercises in assessing and optimizing insulation performance in various building types.

Technology for building envelope optimization and thermal performance enhancement - this course delivers comprehensive expertise in building insulation materials and thermal performance analysis using advanced simulation tools. Students will master heat transfer principles, insulation material properties evaluation, and building envelope design strategies for optimal energy efficiency optimization. The curriculum focuses on practical insulation performance assessment techniques, thermal monitoring methodologies, and advanced insulation technologies integration. Participants will gain hands-on experience with building system integration approaches, hygrothermal analysis methods, and DELPHIN simulation software for moisture transfer analysis and thermal bridge analysis applications. The program emphasizes building insulation BIM integration, insulation cost-effectiveness evaluation, and environmental impact assessment for comprehensive thermal insulation solutions in modern building construction.
